summary:
The Security Council,

Noting the tense situation in the Middle East, considered the report of the Secretary-General on UNDOF, and reaffirmed resolution 1308 (2000),

Expressing concern at events on 15 May and 5 June that jeopardized the ceasefire,

Calls upon parties to implement resolution 338 (1973);

Calls on parties to cooperate with UNDOF's operations and ensure security and access for UN personnel;

Recalls parties' obligation to respect the 1974 Disengagement of Forces Agreement and calls for maximum restraint;

Welcomes UNDOF's efforts on zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;

Requests the Secretary-General to implement recommendations on UNDOF's operational capacity;

Decides to renew UNDOF's mandate for six months, until 30 June 2012;

Requests the Secretary-General to report on developments and measures taken to implement resolution 338 (1973).
